SUMMARY:Choral Meditations
DESCRIPTION:Join us for three lunchtime concerts of music and poetry sung by professional members of the Cathedral Choir. Each 45-minute concert features a selection of remarkable and rarely-heard pieces of music from the medieval and Renaissance periods. This is not a religious service\, although it takes place in the space of the church. It is open to all people of all ages and backgrounds\, free of charge. Join us on your lunch break or passing through downtown for a moment of beautiful music and peace among the busy city!
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/choral-meditations/
LOCATION:The Cathedral Church of St. James\, 106 King St E\, Toronto\, ON M5C 1G6\, Canada\, Old Toronto\, Toronto\, Ontario\, M5C 1G6
CATEGORIES:Live Music,Performing Arts
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/choral-meditations.png
END:VEVENT
