SUMMARY:Luck of the Die - A Deadly Roll; Toronto (Reid's Distillery)
DESCRIPTION:Shamrocks\, shillelaghs\, and shenanigans! Cocktails\, scandal\, and murder await at Luck of the Die – A Deadly Roll. \nLuck is in the air… and so is murder.\nThe Shamrocks & Shillelaghs Casino (aka Reid’s Distillery)\, the most adacious Irish-themed gaming house in town\, is hosting its annual St. Patrick’s High Rollers Event. The air is thick with the scent of whiskey\, the jingle of slot machines\, and the murmur of high-stakes wagers. But behind the revelry\, secrets are brewing\, and before the night is over\, the luck of the Irish may run out for some. \nWhat begins as a sophisticated night of mingling\, cocktails\, and indulgent bites takes a dark turn when a shocking murder shatters the mood. Beneath the flirtation and laughter\, everyone is hiding something — and no one can be trusted. \nThe Plot Thickens…\nAs the evening unfolds\, you’ll sip\, socialize\, and quietly gather clues\, trying to uncover the truth before the killer strikes again. With seven professional actors hidden among the guests\, the line between performer and participant disappears\, and suspicion falls on everyone… including you. \nCan you bet on surviving — or will betrayal be the final course? \n🕯️Event Includes\n\nA welcome drink: Reid’s Cucumber Rose Collin’s\nAn immersive Irish-themed murder mystery\nProfessional actors seamlessly embedded among guests\nA perfect setting for an Irish casino-style mystery\n\n🕯️Available for Purchase\n\nA delicious array of canapés\, appetizers\, and charcuterie boards: MENU\nAn impressive variety of libations: DRINKS\nBribes for the Actors starting at $100 to reveal secret clues (JOKING!)\n\n🕖 Event Schedule\n\n6:00 PM – Doors Open & Mingling\n7:00 PM – 9:00 PM – The Mystery unfolds and is resolved during dinner\n9:00 PM+ Chilling vibes & lingering secrets\n\nFAQs \nHow do I join a group or start a group? \nWhen buying tickets ensure seperate ticket purchase include in comments to be seated together under a groupd name you decide. \nAre we seated with other guests? \nThis is a mingling\, interactive event. There is group seating\, but you may also be seated with other couples if you are a smaller party. \nAre there ID requirements or an age limit for entering the event? \nYes\, ID required for alcohol 19+ and 12+ for an age limit of the event \nWhat are the directions and parking options? \nParking is available on-site in the back\, and paid street parking. \nWhere can I contact the organizer with any questions? \nEmail any questions to chris@slixer.com \nIs my registration/ticket transferrable? \nYes\, you can buy tickets for your group or as a gift. \nCan I update my registration information? \nYes\, either log in to Eventbrite and update or email us at chris@slixer.com \nDo I have to bring my printed ticket to the event? \nA digital copy is acceptable. \nWhat is the refund policy? \nTickets are refundable in exceptional circumstances only.
URL:https://nowtoronto.com/event/luck-of-the-die-a-deadly-roll-toronto-reids-distillery/
LOCATION:Reid’s Distillery Lounge\, 32 Logan Ave\, Toronto\, M4M 2M8
CATEGORIES:Comedy & Improv,Food & Drink
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://nowtoronto.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/02/luck-of-the-die-a-deadly-roll-toronto-reids-distillery.png
END:VEVENT
